{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Out-of-stock products are excluded regardless of relevance score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is most likely at the handoff between inventory filtering and ranking (MOCK-MISS), not inside a single pure function. No OS/network/LLM dependency is required.","test_description":"Wire real filter + ranker modules with a fixture catalog where an out-of-stock item has the highest score; assert it never appears in returned recommendations.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Blocked categories from user settings are excluded.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The bug boundary is user-settings data passed into category filtering (module interaction). A unit test of only the predicate can miss wiring/mapping failures.","test_description":"Use real settings retrieval + category filter modules with a user who blocked category X; assert no product from X is returned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.55,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Browsing-signal products rank above products with no browsing signal.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior can be validated at the scoring/ranking function boundary with deterministic feature inputs; no required external infra or LLM dependency.","test_description":"Call the ranking/scoring function with controlled feature vectors (same everything except browsing signal) and assert the browsing-matching product scores higher.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.45,"Integration":0.45,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Pagination returns the correct page with stable ordering across repeated requests.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Stability depends on ordering + pagination modules working together; unit-testing pagination alone can miss nondeterministic upstream ordering.","test_description":"Run end-to-end recommendation assembly (local modules) on fixed data; request page 2 twice and assert identical product IDs in identical order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"At least one recommendation is from an unseen category (serendipity).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Serendipity is usually enforced across candidate generation and reranking/diversification; a single-function test may miss rule loss at module boundaries.","test_description":"Compose candidate retrieval + diversification/ranking modules with user history that excludes category Y; assert top-N includes at least one item from an unseen category.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Cold-start users get popularity-based recommendations instead of empty results.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears when no-history detection, fallback strategy, and popularity source interact; not just isolated logic.","test_description":"Use real modules for history lookup + fallback selector + popularity ranking with an empty-history user; assert non-empty output and alignment with popularity ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Click tracking stores product ID, list position, and timestamp.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure boundary is between recommendation response context and event persistence schema. Unit tests can miss field mapping and serialization mistakes.","test_description":"Trigger a click through the tracking path using local persistence; assert stored event contains exact product_id, rank position, and a valid timestamp.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"Recommendation generation stays under 200ms for 100,000 products.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Timing regressions depend on real process/runtime/OS effects (REAL-INFRA). Mocked or isolated tests can hide true latency.","test_description":"Run the real recommendation service/process against a 100k-product dataset on representative hardware; measure p95 latency and assert it is <200ms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":9,"description":"Purchased items are deprioritized in later recommendation requests.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Requires state transition across modules: purchase event ingestion/state update plus subsequent ranking. A single-function unit test is insufficient.","test_description":"Issue recommendations, record a purchase of one recommended item via purchase/update path, request recommendations again, and assert purchased item rank drops materially.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":10,"description":"Same user state yields deterministic ranked results across repeated requests.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Non-determinism often comes from module interactions (unordered retrieval, tie-breaking, cache/state wiring), not just one function.","test_description":"With fixed user state and unchanged dataset, invoke